          <msContents class="lemmatic">
            <summary>This manuscript contains commentary on the book of Aphorisms
                            attributed to <persName type="standard" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/287984736" key="n 80119944 ">Hippocrates</persName>. </summary>
            <msItem>
              <author>
                <name type="person" ref="supplied">
                  <persName xml:lang="eng">al-Nīlī</persName>
                  <persName xml:lang="ara">النيلي</persName>
                </name>
              </author>
              <title xml:lang="ara-Latn-x-lc" type="alt">Talkhīs Sharḥ Jālīnūs li
                                Kitāb al-Fuṣūl maʿa Nukat min sharḥ al-Rāzī</title>
              <title xml:lang="ara">تلخيص شرح جالينوس لكتاب الفصول مع نكت من شرح
                                الرازي</title>
              <title xml:lang="ara" type="alt"/>
              <title xml:lang="eng" type="translated">Abridgment of Galen’s Commentary
                                on the Aphorisms with anecdotes [nukat] from ar-Rāzī’s
                                Commentary</title>
              <note>This is a lemmatically arranged commentary. The
                                introduction begins on f. 1b; the beginning of each Book is as
                                follows: Bk1: 1b; Bk 2: 6a (ending at ii. 40; in f. 10b, Bk 2 ends
                                at ii. 40, and then ii. 23 starts); Bk 3: 10a (starting from iii.
                                22's comm.); Bk 4: 12b (ending at iv. 35); Bk 5: 15b; Bk 6: 21a; Bk
                                7: 26b. This is an incomplete copy.</note>
